  "description": "The Solomon knot as a foundation voice. At strandTune=7.02, Ring A (root) and Ring B (fifth) form a built-in power chord. Low filter cutoff (600 Hz) with velocity sensitivity — play hard and the filter rises to 2600 Hz, transforming the bass from sub-thickness to mid-cut power. macroKnot=0.3 brings in a gentle Trefoil asymmetry — Ring A gets a directional pull that gives the low end a subtle pumping character rather than pure symmetry. Saw strands provide harmonic weight for the filter to work against.",
